  "title": "chore(version): bump algoliasearch version to v0.11.0",
  "body": "**Summary**\r\n\r\nfixes: #4916 \r\n\r\nThis PR updates [`algoliasearch`](https://github.com/algolia/algoliasearch-client-javascript) and `@algolia/client-search` to the latest release: [`v0.11.0`](https://github.com/algolia/algoliasearch-client-javascript/releases/tag/4.11.0).\r\n\r\nThis new version introduces a fix on the type of `insideBoundingBox` (see https://github.com/algolia/algoliasearch-client-javascript/pull/1310). `insideBoundingBox` used to only accept a `ReadonlyArray<readonly number[]>;`, wich was conflicting with `instantsearch.js` using it as a `string` #4916 .\r\n\r\n\r\nThe fix introduced in the new @algolia/client-search packages expanded the type of `insideBoundingBox` to also accept a string ([this line](https://github.com/algolia/algoliasearch-client-javascript/blob/dfa7254b1d56b7c339dde39fbb371db369d865fe/packages/client-search/src/types/SearchOptions.ts#L295)). \r\n\r\n```ts\r\n  readonly insideBoundingBox?: ReadonlyArray<readonly number[]> | string;\r\n```\r\n\r\nIn this PR, the packages are updated and the code is made up-to-date with the introduced changes. \r\n\r\n- Typescript ignore comments to avoid typescript error are removed\r\n- Typescript workaround to enforce `string` type is removed\r\n\r\n**Result**\r\n\r\n<img width=\"372\" alt=\"Screenshot 2021-10-19 at 23 11 43\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/33010418/138152708-07d1888d-467f-4b9e-b477-9dc05321e42a.png\">\r\n\r\n\r\n",
